# Optional: local-dev CORS bypass for an OpenAI-compatible API that doesn't
# send CORS headers (e.g. a self-hosted 9router).
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local and set your provider's base origin:
#       VITE_API_PROXY=https://darktama.taile64290.ts.net
# 2. Run `npm run dev`.
# 3. In the app's Settings, set Base URL to:  /proxy/v1
#
# Vite then forwards /proxy/* to VITE_API_PROXY server-side, so the browser
# only talks to localhost and CORS never applies. This is DEV ONLY — it has no
# effect on the production build (the deployed site needs real CORS headers on
# the provider; see the README "CORS" section).
VITE_API_PROXY=
